param_run_num: order of run. Within each session, there are 6 runs
param_cue_type: level of cue; high or low cue
param_trigger_onset: time when scanner started (recorded on psychtoolbox)
param_start_biopac: time when biopac channel was triggered (beginning of experiment
event01_cue_onset: onset when cue was presented on screen
event01_cue_biopac: onset when cue was presented on screen (recorded in biopac)
event01_cue_filename: filename of the cue images that are presented to the participant
event02_expect_displayonset: onset when expectation rating appears on screen
event02_expect_biopac: onset when expectation rating appears on screen (recorded in biopac)
event02_expect_responseonset: onset when expectation rating was reported
event02_expect_angle_label: labels of angles (which category the angle belongs to)
event03_stimulus_biopac: onset when stimulus was delivered (recorded in biopac)
event03_stimulus_C_stim_match: cognitive task: whether stimulus is same/different
event03_stimulusC_reseponseonset: cognitive task: response onset for mental rotation task
event03_stimulusC_RT: cognitive task: reaction time for mental rotation task
event04_actual_displayonset: onset when outcome rating appears on screen
event04_actual_biopac: onset when outcome rating appears on screen (recorded in biopac)
event04_actual_responseonset: onset when outcome rating was reported
event04_actual_angle_label: labels of outcome rating angles (which category the angle belongs to)
param_end_instruct_onset: onset of when end of experiment screen is presented
param_end_biopac: onset of when end of experiment screen is presented (recorded in biopac)
event03_stimulus_P_trigger: confirmation of whether Medoc stimulus was delivered
delay_between_medoc: response time delay between stimulus delivery on stimulus PC and Medoc
